2 (i) As used in this subsection:
3
4 (A) "Carbon capture, utilization and
5 storage technology" means technology that has the principal
6 purpose of capturing, reusing, storing, sequestering or
7 using carbon dioxide emissions to prevent carbon dioxide
8 from entering the atmosphere;
9
10 (B) "Enhanced oil and gas recovery" means
11 all existing and future technologies or methods to recover
12 oil and gas beyond traditional primary and secondary
13 recovery methods, including technology to optimize
14 development and recovery of oil and gas resources in new
15 fields.
16
17 (ii) The taxpayer seeking the exemption shall
18 complete an application for the exemption on a form and in
19 the manner prescribed by the department;
20
21 (iii) To qualify for the exemption under this
22 subsection, the crude oil and natural gas shall be produced
