1 by means of enhanced oil and gas recovery from projects
2 using carbon capture, utilization and storage technology;
3
4 (iv) The carbon dioxide captured and used in the
5 enhanced oil and gas recovery to produce crude oil and
6 natural gas shall be from a carbon dioxide source
7 originating within the state of Wyoming;
8
9 (v) To ensure that the crude oil and natural gas
10 production by means of enhanced oil and gas recovery
11 satisfies the conditions of this subsection, the department
12 may consult with the public service commission and the
13 Wyoming oil and gas conservation commission before
14 approving the exemption under this subsection;
15
16 (vi) The department may promulgate rules as
17 necessary to implement this subsection;
18
19 (vii) Not later than November 1 of each year,
20 the department shall report to the joint revenue interim
21 committee and the joint minerals, business and economic
22 development interim committee on the use of the exemption
23 under this subsection and the associated revenue impacts.
